, another Peruvian dish. <p>

Both dishes share the use of a seasoned ground beef as their main ingredient. The ground beef is prepared with cooked onions, chopped boiled egg, raisins and olives.</p>
<p>

<it>Arroz tapado</it> is made by tightly packing rice and the seasoned ground beef into a bowl. The bowl is then turned over onto a plate and removed so that only the ingredients remain. </p>
<p>

The dish is often decorated with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../640/341640.xml">
cilantro</link> and served with <link>
salsa criolla</link>, an onion dressing with <link>
aji</link>, lemon juice, olive oil and white vinegar.</p>



